Const is a pretty good example, the closest I can think to emulating it in es5 is something like:<p>Object.defineProperty(this, &#x27;five&#x27;, {
  enumerable: true, 
  writable: false, 
  value: 5, 
  configurable: false
});<p>If in global scope, &#x27;five&#x27; will look like a const.<p>WeakMap and WeakSet have polyfills with minor caveats.<p>I guess you&#x27;re defining language features as not &quot;syntactic sugar&quot; if they can&#x27;t be absolutely 100% polyfilled.
